2. Rock, Paper, Scissors

Concept:
Player chooses Rock, Paper, or Scissors; computer chooses randomly.

Why it’s good:

Fast and fun

Introduces enums or constants

Core features:

Menu-driven input

Random computer choice

Win/lose/draw logic

Score tracking

Example twist:
Play best of 3 or best of 5.